  "prompt": "What are some good auto biographies?",
  "response": "Sure! Here are some highly regarded autobiographies across various genres and time periods:\n\n1. **\"The Autobiography of Malcolm X\" by Malcolm X and Alex Haley** - Chronicles the life of the African-American activist and provides profound insights into race relations in America.\n\n2. **\"Long Walk to Freedom\" by Nelson Mandela** - The inspiring life story of South Africa's first black president and his struggle against apartheid.\n\n3. **\"Becoming\" by Michelle Obama** - A personal and intimate account of the former First Lady's life, from childhood to her time in the White House.\n\n4. **\"Dreams from My Father: A Story of Race and Inheritance\" by Barack Obama** - A deeply introspective and beautifully written narrative exploring identity and family heritage.\n\n5. **\"Steve Jobs\" by Walter Isaacson** - Although technically a biography, Isaacson wrote this based on extensive interviews with Jobs himself, offering dramatic insights into the life of Apple's co-founder.\n\n6. **\"I Know Why the Caged Bird Sings\" by Maya Angelou** - The first of seven autobiographical works by the poet and writer, offering a powerful depiction of overcoming adversity.\n\n7. **\"The Diary of a Young Girl\" by Anne Frank** - The poignant and painfully candid diary of a young Jewish girl hiding during the Nazi occupation of the Netherlands.\n\n8. **\"Open\" by Andre Agassi** - This candid autobiography by the tennis star reveals struggles with identity and personal challenges behind his sports career.\n\n9. **\"Bossypants\" by Tina Fey** - A hilarious and insightful memoir by the comedian, actress, and writer.\n\n10. **\"Me\" by Elton John** - An honest and engaging account of the music icon's life, career, and personal battles.\n\nThese autobiographies offer both historical insights and deeply personal narratives, making them compelling reads.",
